      "title": "Module 2: Build your toolkit, not your substitutes",
      "text": "A quick but vital distinction. A substitute tries to replace the cigarette — gum, sweets, vapes, another nicotine product. Avoid all of these. They keep you believing you've lost something that needs replacing, and the nicotine ones literally keep the addiction alive. There is no substitute for a thing you no longer need.\n\nA tool, by contrast, doesn't replace the cigarette — it helps you ride out a passing craving while your wiring updates. You've already learned several this week:\n\n• The 3-minute watch: a craving is a wave; time it and let it pass.\n\n• The long exhale: slow your breathing to down-shift stress directly.\n\n• Name the monster: relabel the urge as the addiction, not you.\n\n• Trade the picture: swap the flattering close-up for the whole reel.\n\n• The honest question: \"enjoy it, or just end the itch?\"\n\nToday you choose which tools you'll lead with, and add a couple of behavioural ones: a glass of water, a two-minute walk, a quick stretch, a message to someone, a specific task you can pick up."
